  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "proposed a new electronic health record (EHR) sharing scheme by combining a blockchain with the InterPlanetary File System on a mobile platform.",
    "In their work, they presented an Ethereum blockchain that performs EHR transactions and a mobile application prototype connected to an Amazon server [20].In another study, Li et al.",
    "proposed a data aggregation scheme that saves the health records of patients on the blockchain.",
    "A group authentication mechanism was also designed for authorized users (e.g., patients, doctors, caregivers, family, and friends) to access the health records of patients.",
    "Although saving the health records of patients on the blockchain seems to be advantageous in terms of security, saving big patient data to the blockchain creates a disadvantage in terms of system performance [21]."
  ],
